36:
Coming for me in the middle of the
night?! I trusted you!
40:
Excuse me? Just who do you take
me for?
44:
A person who lacks a sense of ethics
and morals?
48:
Wow, rude! Here I am on my best
behavior too!
63: There are stars all around us!
68:
A pretty sight, isn't it? This always
happens after it rains, so it's one of
my favorite hideaways.
69:
I know Stella enjoys these types of
quiet locations, but what about you,
Alk?
74:
Do you even need to ask? I'm blown
away...
80:
Consider this an apology for all the
chaos I've caused.
83:
It's nice, but you could've just invited
me here without the midnight scare.
86:
Still, I appreciate you sharing this
with us!
99:
I've always loved the stars, ever
since I was a kid.
102:
Why so shocked? Wicked Witch I
may be, but even I was young once.
104:
Granted, it was a long, long time
ago...
113: The very first spell I ever learned.
116:
My path to becoming a witch all
started with a simple wish—to travel
to the ends of the stars.
117:
Not that I ever managed to make
that come true.
124:
Alk, do you still want to learn about
your past?
126:
Find out who you are and where you
came from?
127: Or are you afraid to learn the truth?
131: I'd be lying if I said I wasn't scared...
133:
But not as much as I was before.
Staying ignorant is pretty frightening
too.
139:
I'm glad the first person Stella ever
met was you.
142:
Hey, I was only with her for a week!
When we stepped out of town the
first time, Light—
147: Alk. Belsidia. Look at the stars!
150: So far away, and only flying further.
157:
Understanding the beauty of a
starry sky is one thing.
159:
But are you prepared to face the
night without lights to guide the way?
160:
When the time comes, I hope you
find the courage to face what's
ahead...
179:
Nothing beats spending time with
my two favorite cuties.
